Talyfocous Privacy Policy
Last updated: July 2, 2026
Summary
Talyfocous is a Windows desktop accounting application for small businesses and accountants. Your
company data is stored on your computer by default. We do not operate a central server that stores your
books, inventory, or payroll.
Information the app stores on your device
• Accounting data you enter: invoices, journal vouchers, chart of accounts, inventory, payroll, bank
reconciliation files, and reports.
• User accounts and settings you configure in the app (user names, passwords, and app preferences).
• Company files and fiscal-year data saved in a local database on your PC.
Information we do not collect
• We do not collect, transmit, or sell your accounting data to third parties.
• We do not receive your payment card details.
• We do not track your browsing activity inside or outside the app.
• We do not build advertising profiles from your use of Talyfocous.
Optional features
If you choose to use optional features, limited data may be involved:
• Microsoft Store subscription: if you subscribe through the Microsoft Store, Microsoft processes
payment and subscription status. Talyfocous checks whether your subscription is active using the
Windows Store API on your device. We do not receive your card number.
• Company Network Link: if you connect employee computers to a main computer on your office
network, data is shared only within your local network as you configure it.
• Cloud backup (optional): if you sign in and use cloud backup, your backup file is stored in your
Firebase cloud storage account that you connect. This is optional and controlled by you.
How information is used
• To run the app and save your work on your computer.
• To let linked computers on your network access data from the main computer, when you enable that
feature.
• To verify an active Microsoft Store subscription, when you install from the Store.
• To upload or restore a backup, only when you choose cloud backup.
Data retention and deletion
Data remains on your device until you delete it in the app, uninstall the application, or remove company
files. If you use cloud backup, you can delete backups from your cloud storage account. Uninstalling the
app does not automatically delete files in your user data folder unless you remove them manually.
Children's privacy
Talyfocous is business software and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
personal information from children.
Changes to this policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this document
will be revised when changes are made.
